Create and submit an evaluation run.

In a normal terminal session, omitting --challenge-pack-version and/or
--deployments launches an interactive picker so you can scroll through
available challenge packs, versions, input sets, and deployments and press
Enter to select them.

For CI and other non-interactive use, keep passing explicit IDs via flags.

Usage:
  agentclash run create [flags]

Flags:
      --challenge-pack-version string   Challenge pack version ID (optional in a TTY; prompted when omitted)
      --deployments strings             Agent deployment IDs (optional in a TTY; prompted when omitted)
      --follow                          Follow run events after creation
  -h, --help                            help for create
      --input-set string                Challenge input set ID (optional)
      --name string                     Run name (optional)

Global Flags:
      --api-url string     API base URL (overrides config)
      --json               Output in JSON format
      --no-color           Disable color output
      --non-interactive    Disable interactive prompts (also honored: CI=true, AGENTCLASH_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, --json, no TTY)
  -o, --output string      Output format: table, json, yaml
  -q, --quiet              Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose            Enable debug output on stderr
  -w, --workspace string   Workspace ID (overrides config)
      --yes                Skip confirmation prompts
